src/lib/components/DashInteractiveGraphv.description:
An interactive graphviz renderer.

Renders the dot language in the browser. It allows for panning and zooming
and node selection. Changes in the dot_source will be animated.

Graphviz is run in the browser via viz.js, so it can be computationally
intensive.

id.description: The ID used to identify this component in Dash callbacks.

selected.description: The ID of the selected node.

dot_source.description: The dot language source of the graph

style.description:
Styling to be applied to the graph container. You may want to change
your graphviz background to transparent.

fit_button_style.description: The style of the fit button.

fit_button_content.description: The text content of the fit button, by default it is an small square unicode character.

setProps.description:
Dash-assigned callback that should be called to report property changes
to Dash, to make them available for callbacks.
